TITLE: Wall Street's top analysts believe these stocks could be long-term winners
SUMMARY: TipRanks analyst ranking service pinpoints Wall Street's best-performing stocks, like Square and Twilio.

TITLE: Musk: 'Dream come true' to see fully stacked SpaceX Starship rocket during prep for orbital launch
SUMMARY: Elon Musk's SpaceX stacked a Starship prototype rocket on top of a Super Heavy rocket booster for the first time Friday morning.

TITLE: Robinhood shares jump nearly 8% as it closes out wild week
SUMMARY: Robinhood shares rose Friday as the newly public stock trading app closes out a wild week of trading.

TITLE: Michael Farr: Buying opportunities abound, even as the market trades near record levels
SUMMARY: The major averages are churning near highs, despite an environment of uncertainty. Michael Farr identifies five stocks that could be a plum opportunity.

TITLE: Virgin Galactic reopens ticket sales, with prices starting at $450,000 per seat
SUMMARY: Virgin Galactic delivered second-quarter results after the market closed on Thursday and announced the reopening of ticket sales for spaceflights.

TITLE: Space company Maxar stock drops 14% after delaying launch of next-generation satellites
SUMMARY: Space company Maxar Technologies shares dropped in trading Thursday after it announced another delay to the launch of its next-generation imagery satellites.

TITLE: Wells Fargo postpones return-to-office plans by a month amid coronavirus surge
SUMMARY: Wells Fargo is joining a growing list of corporations that are pushing back return dates or mandating vaccines amid a nationwide covid surge.

TITLE: Astra stock jumps 24% as rocket builder targets late August for first launch since going public
SUMMARY: Publicly traded rocket builder Astra will go for its first launch of the year later this month, planning to transport a Pentagon payload to orbit.

TITLE: JPMorgan takes stake in healthcare start-up, will begin offering service to employees in fall
SUMMARY: Vera, founded in 2008, aims to improve outcomes for workers and reduce costs for companies by making primary care teams accountable for the health of employees.

TITLE: Vanguard says it will give employees $1,000 to get the Covid-19 vaccine
SUMMARY: Vanguard is offering its employees $1,000 to get vaccinated against the coronavirus.

TITLE: Bezos' Blue Origin calls Musk's Starship 'immensely complex & high risk' for NASA moon missions
SUMMARY: Jeff Bezos’ Blue Origin blasted NASA’s decision to award Elon Musk’s SpaceX the sole contract to build a lunar lander.

TITLE: Robinhood surges 50% in second day of wild trading, up 100% this week
SUMMARY: Cathie Wood purchased 89,622 shares of HOOD on Tuesday in ARK Fintech Innovation ETF, a position worth roughly $4.2 million.

TITLE: Elon Musk's photos show SpaceX rolling out its massive rocket booster for Starship
SUMMARY: SpaceX on Tuesday rolled out the rocket booster that the company plans to use to launch the first Starship orbital flight.

TITLE: What the SEC chair's comments on crypto mean for a possible bitcoin ETF
SUMMARY: SEC chief Gary Gensler says crypto assets need a lot more regulation before they can move forward.

TITLE: SpaceX says Starlink has about 90,000 users as the internet service gains subscribers
SUMMARY: SpaceX continues to add subscribers to its Starlink satellite internet service, with Elon Musk's company saying it now serves about 90,000 users globally.

TITLE: SolarEdge shares surge after quarterly earnings top estimates
SUMMARY: The residential solar power company’s shares gained on Tuesday morning following strong quarterly results.

TITLE: Rocket Companies jumps as mortgage lender announces expansion into solar
SUMMARY: Rocket Companies on Monday announced plans to enter the solar energy market.

TITLE: Utilities are struggling to keep the lights on as fires, drought plague California
SUMMARY: Droughts, wildfires and other extreme events fueled by climate change have put grid operators in the Western U.S. under pressure.

TITLE: Top Wall Street analysts are betting on more gains for these stocks as earnings continue
SUMMARY: TipRanks analyst ranking service pinpoints Wall Street's best-performing stocks, like Tesla & Nike

TITLE: Government denies Bezos' protest of NASA awarding lunar lander contract to Musk's SpaceX
SUMMARY: The U.S. GAO denied a protest by Jeff Bezos' Blue Origin that NASA wrongly awarded a lucrative astronaut lunar lander contract solely to Elon Musk's SpaceX.

TITLE: MicroStrategy CEO defends debt-financed bitcoin buys, compares it to investing early in Facebook
SUMMARY: "If I could borrow $1 billion and buy Facebook a decade ago for 1% interest, I think I would've done quite well," MicroStrategy's Michael Saylor told CNBC.

TITLE: SEC slaps new disclosure requirements on Chinese IPOs amid Beijing's crackdown
SUMMARY: The Securities and Exchange Commission said Friday it will now require additional disclosures from Chinese companies seeking a listing on U.S. stock exchanges.

TITLE: Chevron, Exxon earnings top estimates amid recovery in oil and gas prices
SUMMARY: Chevron and Exxon  reported profits for the second straight quarter as higher demand for petroleum products and a jump in oil and gas prices boosted operations.

TITLE: The U.S. economy is bigger than it was pre-pandemic, but Covid could still decide what happens next
SUMMARY: The U.S. economy is now larger than it was before the pandemic, but its growth rate may have peaked this year at a much slower pace than expected.

TITLE: Space start-up Varda, founded by SpaceX and Founders Fund veterans, aims to build factories in orbit
SUMMARY: Varda Space Industries, a start-up founded less than a year ago by a pair with experience at SpaceX and Founders Fund, has raised more than $50 million.

TITLE: Robinhood CEO on the meme stock craze: 'I think it's a real thing'
SUMMARY: Robinhood's Vlad Tenev said retail clients who invest in so-called meme stocks give embattled companies access to capital they otherwise wouldn't have.

TITLE: Wall Street employees begin to mask up again as Citigroup tells workers of new mandate
SUMMARY: For a few glorious weeks, Wall Street employees who were vaccinated against Covid-19 could ditch their masks at the office. That's ending.

TITLE: Halfway through earnings season, the 'peak everything' story may need to be put on hold
SUMMARY: Not only are earnings blowing out estimates by a wide margin, but companies are raising guidance for the remainder of 2021.

TITLE: U.S. Marshals Service hires custodian to hold crypto seized in criminal activity
SUMMARY: The U.S. Marshals Service has hired crypto custodian Anchorage Digital to custody its seized cryptocurrency.

TITLE: Fed holds rates near zero, says economy has gotten better even with pandemic worries
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve on Wednesday held its benchmark interest rate near zero and said the economy continues to progress despite concerns over the pandemic spread.
